#################################################################
    # Triples and Links
#################################################################

### Degree to Course Guide Link (via hasCourse) - Note: Ontology defines `guide:hasCourse` from Degree -> Course. I will create a generic Course instance for the offering or link directly if possible, but strict ontology requires intermediate Class instances. Let's assume the course guide represents an instance of the degree curriculum.
<http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/course-53001736> rdf:type sch:CourseInstance ;
                                                   sch:name "Sistemas De Control Y Automatización"^^xsd:string .

### Course Guide to Degree Link (via hasCourse) - Note: Ontology defines `guide:hasCourse` from Degree -> Range guide:Course. I will link the specific course instance here if possible, or just use properties available on CourseGuide directly for attributes like credits/teaching period.
<http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/course-53001736> rdf:type sch:CourseInstance ;
                                                   guide:numberOfCredits 3^^xsd:decimal .

### Lecturer to Course Guide Link (via director/instructor) - Ontology has `sch:director` and `sch:instructor`. I will use both or one. Let's use `guide:sch:director` if available? No, ontology defines `sch:director` from guide:CourseGuide -> guide:Lecturer.
<http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/course-53001736> sch:director <http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/lecturer-jose-sebastian> .

### Course Guide to Syllabus Link (via hasSyllabus) - Ontology defines `guide:hasSyllabus` from guide:CourseGuide -> guide:Syllabus.
<http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/course-53001736> guide:hasSyllabus <http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/syllabus-53001736> .

### Syllabus to Items Link (via hasItem) - Ontology defines `guide:hasItem` from guide:Syllabus -> guide:SyllabusItem.
<http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/syllabus-53001736> guide:hasItem <http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/item-programacion-automatas>,
                                                          <http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/item-modelo-estado>.

### Course Guide to Competencies Link (via hasCompetency) - Ontology defines `guide:hasCompetency` from guide:CourseGuide -> guide:Competency.
<http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/course-53001736> guide:hasCompetency <http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/comp-MUAR-CB06>,
                                                                      <http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/comp-MUII-CG08>.

### Course Guide to Learning Results Link (via hasLearningResult) - Ontology defines `guide:hasLearningResult` from guide:CourseGuide -> guide:LearningResult.
<http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/course-53001736> guide:hasLearningResult <http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/ra-RA101>,
                                                                             <http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/ra-RA102>.

### Course Guide to Evaluation System Link (via hasEvaluation) - Ontology defines `guide:hasEvaluation` from guide:CourseGuide -> guide:EvaluationSystem.
<http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/course-53001736> guide:hasEvaluation <http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/eval-system-ordinaria>.

### Evaluation System to Trial Link (via hasEvaluationTrial) - Ontology defines `guide:hasEvaluationTrial` from guide:EvaluationSystem -> guide:EvaluationTrial.
<http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/eval-system-ordinaria> guide:hasEvaluationTrial <http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/trial-tarea-1>.

### Course Guide to Schedule Link (via courseSchedule) - Ontology defines `sch:courseSchedule` from guide:CourseGuide -> guide:Schedule.
<http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/course-53001736> sch:courseSchedule <http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/schedule-53001736>.

### Schedule to Event Link (via eventSchedule) - Ontology defines `sch:eventSchedule` from guide:Schedule -> guide:ScheduleEvent.
<http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/schedule-53001736> sch:eventSchedule <http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/event-tarea-1>.

### Course Guide to Didactic Resource Link (via hasDidacticResource) - Ontology defines `guide:hasDidacticResource` from guide:CourseGuide -> guide:DidacticResource.
