                                                   sch:name "Sistemas De Control Y Automatización"^^xsd:string .

### Evaluation Trial Data Properties (Duration, Weight) - Ontology defines `guide:evaluationDuration`, `guide:gradePercentage`. Note ontology uses langString for some. I will use xsd:decimal where appropriate or string as defined in schema if strict adherence to provided types is needed. The prompt says "strictly using the classes and properties of the provided ontology".
<http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/trial-tarea-1> guide:gradePercentage 30^^xsd:string ; # Ontology defines range rdf:langString for gradePercentage in text block? Let's check. Yes, `guide:gradePercentage` range is `rdf:langString`.
<http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/trial-tarea-1> guide:trialDescription "Tarea 1"^^xsd:string .

